Author: Ashley.Livetree
Title: [BOUNTY][ICO][BBB] 🔮 LiveTree ADEPT [SED]: OWN THE FUTURE OF ENTERTAINMENT! 🔮
Body: LiveTree Bounty update (BB details below)  We have been working hard since the close of the sale. The total raise was 1127.52868 ETH and 60.0527767 BTC. Seed Incentive, Founders pools are reserved and locked. The people in the referrer program have received their Seed. The Lottery pool has been allocated and is awaiting distribution. Sale token pool and final burn amount is pending underwriting. We are making good progress on building the future of entertainment, check out our 'LiveTree progress update' on Medium.  We have yet to receive any funds from the underwriters. We are still in talks and are working diligently to progress the matter and seek alternatives, if necessary.  To date we have raised less than the total amount required for the bounty campaign qualification, however, we are pretty close to the target and we recognise bounty participants have worked hard! To thank them for their efforts, which the bounty manager Sylon has 'championed' and we agree with, we have proceeded with the Seed distribution.  We are now airdropping the tokens associated with the spreadsheet and we look forward to hearing your suggestions for our listing strategy.  A spreadsheet will be made available here detailing the allocation wallet addresses and the amount. Naturally, the BB is contingent on subsequent funds being available. We would like to work with bounty participants to further enhance our listing strategy.  We have created a separate area in the website for bounty participants to discuss this strategy as a community.  We will require registering only if you want to participate in the BB strategy, at this stage it is completely OPTIONAL.  We will need proof of authentication to make sure nobody claims your work so we will need a BitcoinTalk associated handle and an email sent from that handle to “Ashley.Livetree” on BitcoinTalk with the subject “PASSWORD: <INSERT A MEMORABLE PASSWORD> and put your wallet address in the body.  Your wallet address, password and username will be used to access the separate area of the website.  Please send a message from your BitcoinTalk username by the latest May 16th 2018, 13:00 UTC to Ashley.Livetree with the subject “PASSWORD: <INSERT A MEMORABLE PASSWORD> and your wallet address in the body.  If you have any questions about the distribution spreadsheet please address them directly to Ashley on Telegram or an administrator of this thread.

Author: Sylon
Title: [BOUNTY][ICO][BBB] 🔮 LiveTree ADEPT [SED]: OWN THE FUTURE OF ENTERTAINMENT! 🔮
Body: Distribution spreadsheet is already built and ready to be used to distribute the tokens.  Quote from: JesusCryptos on April 21, 2018, 10:53:52 AM After having weared their signature for so many months I think bounty hunters would deserve some consideration and to be when they will be paid. It is a huge lack of respect to keep silent on that.  I agree on the disrespect thing but LiveTree has the information, not me. I've been asking multiple times and every time, the answer is the same: "update will be provided soon".  By the way, you are free to remove your signature and avatar since weeks.  Quote from: BTCHakan on April 21, 2018, 06:18:35 PM   There is a conversation about KYC for bounty distribution. An admin said "You need the KYC for Bounty". I didn't see this requirement on the bounty announcement. Sylon, would you like to clear us about this subject.  https://t.me/LiveTreeAdept/22065           This is a pure nonsense. I have no idea of who this community manager is, and KYC was never included in the bounty campaign rules. I don't know why he's made such statement while he was not involded ever in the bounty campaign creation... I have making a severe investigation right now to clear that point. I will provide new information in this thread as soon as I will have.

Author: roycilik
Title: [BOUNTY][ICO][BBB] 🔮 LiveTree ADEPT [SED]: OWN THE FUTURE OF ENTERTAINMENT! 🔮
Body: please read before you join. you can find the answer on here  Quote from: Sylon on October 27, 2017, 01:02:50 AM Rules : Participants in this campaign have to be at least a Member Full Member to wear our signature. Minimum 20 constructive posts per week. If you don't reach 20 posts before a Friday, you will not receive any stake for the current week. We will pay 25 posts per week maximum. This campaign works on a pay-per-post model. But you will still have to do a minimum amount of posts per week. Posts made in the following sections (and all their child boards) will not be counted as valid posts: Marketplace; Off-topic; Archival; Marketplace (Altcoins). Posts such as "hello", "good luck", "love this project", or any other unsubstantial posts will not be counted as valid. Posts with less than 80 characters will not be counted as valid posts. Every signature campaign participant has to wear our avatar (except participants with Member rank). Participants with red trust score will not be accepted. Multiple accounts are not allowed and will result in banning you from our campaign. If you decide to leave us for another campaign, please write it down in this thread so we could check if you deserve to reserve your current week stakes (= if you posted 20 constructive posts). If you don't, we will not distribute your current week stakes.

Author: gerymakgyaer
Title: [BOUNTY][ICO][BBB] 🔮 LiveTree ADEPT [SED]: OWN THE FUTURE OF ENTERTAINMENT! 🔮
Body: 5 Cryptocurrencies To Consider  The world of crypto is larger than anyone could have anticipated a decade ago. Naturally, the market is becoming crowded with hundreds of new tokens being implemented every year. We’ve picked five key ones to consider.  Bitcoin  Bitcoin is without a doubt responsible for most of the hype that has arisen around cryptocurrencies. It was the first cryptocurrency, originating back in 2009. Now it is still the largest in terms of total valuation and market capitalisation. Due to this unprecedented success, Bitcoin’s protocol rules have become seemingly set in stone as they are viewed as a professional standard. This could provide tricky when it comes to implementing new systems.  Ethereum  Ethereum is a platform allowing blockchain technology to create various tools such as smart contracts. It is truly paving the way for cryptocurrencies to advance in the future. It is leaning towards the fast development approach, allowing multiple versions to be released yearly, adapting to the newest ideas and tools available. Ethereum has been on a stable rise since this autumn — some short and sharp dips notwithstanding — but for how long will it last?  Litecoin  Litecoin is the first altcoin. It’s primary purpose is to be used for transactions that are lower level than Bitcoin and many other cryptos as it has always been promoted as the ‘silver to Bitcoin’s gold’. The pitfall for this type of currency has always been simple: what if the bigger value coins develop some layers for lower-value transactions? Litecoin would be pushed right out of the market.  Bitcoin Cash  In many ways, this coin is a clone of the one it is named after. Bitcoin Cash was created last summer by people concerned about the original Bitcoin’s ability to scale. Bitcoin Cash is able to handle additional block sizes, allowing more information to be stored within the code. Bitcoin Cash was quite popular when it first came out, but it is hard to tell what awaits this crypto in the future, especially when it is still pretty much in the shadow of its predecessor.  LiveTree Seed  Built upon an already operational two-year-old company, Seed token has just entered its main sale after the successful pre-sale and is getting more traction every day.  Seed is taking on the entire entertainment industry, hoping to move the power away from the likes of Harvey Weinstein to the people who actually watch the content. Powering not only the viewers but creators as well, LiveTree’s project’s future is looking very bright. The first projects from the upcoming Blossom TV platform are starting to emerge, such as the world’s first cryptocurrency game show, CryptoShare, and a film about the sector, Decentralized.  https://medium.com/@LiveTree/5-cryptocurrencies-to-consider-a089dcc91fdb

Author: filsid
Title: [BOUNTY][ICO][BBB] 🔮 LiveTree ADEPT [SED]: OWN THE FUTURE OF ENTERTAINMENT! 🔮
Body: CryptoShare - one of a kind  Imagine earning while watching a game show. This will soon be a reality when our new show CryptoShare comes into fruition. Exclusively premiering on our new online channel Blossom TV, this game show looks not only to entertain but to educate at the same time.    CryptoShare will see 7 ICO Teams competing against one another for the ultimate prize — 1,000,000 Seed Tokens, partially owned by the audience, which shall also pick the challenges. Over a span of 5 weeks the participants shall be pitted against one another, judged by a panel of known Crypto Specialists, until only one team triumphs. The viewers then get to choose what to do with 45% of the Tokens won by their supported ICO team, with 5% being donated to a chosen charity.  CryptoShare will also help to educate millions of people about the potential uses of Blockchain technology and to raise awareness about the impact it has on our society. We are entering a new age of entertainment and we would be delighted to have you join us on this voyage of discovery.  Blossom TV, the home of CryptoShare is our new video streaming platform that is on it’s way to your browser, iOS and Android screens. Blockchain is in the heart of everything we do at LiveTree and we are utilising the many advantages of technology to decentralize the entertainment industry, providing more diverse content, opportunities and a different business model in order to disrupt the industry.  https://medium.com/@LiveTree/cryptoshare-one-of-a-kind-7826d46d297f

Title: [BOUNTY][ICO][BBB] 🔮 LiveTree ADEPT [SED]: OWN THE FUTURE OF ENTERTAINMENT! 🔮
Body: I think Sylon won't bother to respond. It's clearly stated in the Rules in the opening post and I posted it below, please read the highlighted texts...  Quote Rules : This campaign is limited to 1000 participants. Only twitter accounts with more than 1000 followers will be allowed. Twitter campaign stakes ARE NOT distributed on a weekly basis. Do not RT and like tweets that are answers to other users. Do not RT and like tweets that are more than two weeks old. Do not post a Twitter report in this thread; we will analyze Twitter data on our own. We reserve the right to not consider your twitter account eligible for this campaign, even if you meet the prerequisites. You don't have to post reports in this thread! If at the end of the campaign, you tweeted more than 2000 times since your registration date, some of your retweets may not be counted. The same rule applies for likes. We won't accept participants that use Newbie, Jr. Member or Member bitcointalk accounts to list their twitter account. We will also remove you if your account is not active.

Twitter campaign stakes ARE NOT distributed on a weekly basis. Do not RT and like tweets that are answers to other users. Do not RT and like tweets that are more than two weeks old. Do not post a Twitter report in this thread; we will analyze Twitter data on our own. We reserve the right to not consider your twitter account eligible for this campaign, even if you meet the prerequisites. You don't have to post reports in this thread! If at the end of the campaign, you tweeted more than 2000 times since your registration date, some of your retweets may not be counted. The same rule applies for likes. ----------------> We won't accept participants that use Newbie, Jr. Member or Member bitcointalk accounts to list their twitter account. We will also remove you if your account is not active.<--------------------

Author: Sylon
Title: [BOUNTY][ICO][BBB] 🔮 LiveTree ADEPT [SED]: OWN THE FUTURE OF ENTERTAINMENT! 🔮
Body: WEBSITE    BITCOINTALK THREAD    WHITEPAPER    TWITTER    BLOG    TELEGRAM    FACEBOOK  What is LiveTree ADEPT ?  ADEPT: Advanced Decentralized Entertainment Platform for Transparent distribution.   LiveTree is an established, socially responsible crowdfunding company based in London, UK. Over the last two years, it has captured 5% of the UK crowdfunding market (in the film and content category) and forged partnerships with several leading names in entertainment, including the British Film Institute Future Film, the Screen Arts Institute, Red Rock Entertainment and 20 independent organizations. LiveTree has compiled a contact directory of 14,000 entertainment suppliers and thousands of individuals who work across film, TV and content.  LiveTree is set to embark on a new project to addresses these industry challenges. This white paper sets out its solution across three key areas: LiveTree ADEPT: A decentralized platform that reimagines entertainment’s value chain: the process of content creation, funding and distribution. Distribution is via Blossom, a game-changing, decentralized digital rights management system that is set to revolutionize how content is interacted with, shared and consumed.   This bounty campaign will be managed by Sylon.  If you have any technical question regarding this project, please ask it in announcement thread.  Stakes you will get from the campaign will allow you to get SED tokens at the end of the campaign. You will receive 1.75% of all SED tokens, based on your number of stakes.  This campaign will last until the end of LiveTree Adept ICO (17th March 2018 1st April 2018, or before if the ICO is a success).   This bounty campaign is based on a BBB (Bounties Buy Back) model: a portion of the bounties tokens that will be distributed through this campaign will be purchased back, at ICO price, after the token sale end.   50% of the SED tokens from the bounty campaign will be purchased back, in exchange of ETH. Note: All dollar values are approximate and depend on ETH exchange rate. Note': Bounty is only available after the min. raise has been met which is approx. $1.5m  There is a sliding scale so you will always get a guaranteed buy-back for every $100 backed $1 is available for bounty buy back.  The buy-back price is guaranteed at 1000 SED = 1ETH.  Thus, bounty campaign participants can be paid in SED or SED + ETH, the choice is up to you.   Sections  Campaign 1: Signature campaign : 40% allocation Campaign 2: Articles campaign : 37.5% allocation Campaign 3: Twitter campaign : 6.5% allocation Campaign 4: Translations campaign : 15% allocation Campaign 5: Telegram campaign : 1 % allocation   General Terms  Stakes will be distributed every week, on Friday. First stake distribution will occur on 3rd November. We reserve the right to remove you from any campaign at any time if we think you are not honest, or spam the forum. We reserve the right to remove you from any campaign without explaining why we removed you. In case we remove you from the campaign for any reason, we reserve the right to delete your stakes. We may not accept you in the campaign for any reasons. If your rank change during the campaign, you must contact the campaign manager, Sylon, in a bitcointalk PM. If you does not meet the minimum amount of posts, you will not receive any stake for the current week. But you will not be removed from the campaign. Using multi-accounts, cheating and spamming are not allowed. It will results getting all of your accounts permanently banned from all my campaigns.  You just read General Terms. Specific campaigns may have other added rules. Therefore, please read other campaigns rules to have specific rules.    Campaign 1: Signatures campaign  Weekly Campaign Rates : Members : $5 per post (in SED tokens) / Members are not accepted anymore Full members : $25 per post (in SED tokens) Senior members : $35 per post (in SED tokens) Hero members : $40 per post (in SED tokens) Legendary members : $55 per post (in SED tokens)  Rules : Participants in this campaign have to be at least a Member Full Member to wear our signature. Minimum 20 constructive posts per week. If you don't reach 20 posts before a Friday, you will not receive any stake for the current week. We will pay 25 posts per week maximum. This campaign works on a pay-per-post model. But you will still have to do a minimum amount of posts per week. Posts made in the following sections (and all their child boards) will not be counted as valid posts: Marketplace; Off-topic; Archival; Marketplace (Altcoins). Posts such as "hello", "good luck", "love this project", or any other unsubstantial posts will not be counted as valid. Posts with less than 80 characters will not be counted as valid posts. Every signature campaign participant has to wear our avatar (except participants with Member rank). Participants with red trust score will not be accepted. Multiple accounts are not allowed and will result in banning you from our campaign. If you decide to leave us for another campaign, please write it down in this thread so we could check if you deserve to reserve your current week stakes (= if you posted 20 constructive posts). If you don't, we will not distribute your current week stakes.  How to participate :  Post a message in this thread with the following informations (don't forget the #JOIN). Rates :  1 article = 1 stake  Rules : Your article has to be very high-quality written. You must be followed by at least 500 users or your article has to be read more than 1000 times. Your article must be unique. It can not be a copied and pasted article. It must be written in English. It has to be published publicly. Private articles won't be accepted. It must be 500 words long or more. It must have a link to our website; adept.livetree.com and Bitcointalk thread. We reserve the right to consider any article not eligible for this campaign, without giving any reason.  How to participate : Send me a PM with the following informations. Your PM title will have to be "LiveTree Articles Campaign Application".  Code: Bitcointalk username: Website link: How many daily visits: Traffic proof:  If your website is eligible for this campaign, I will reply you with a positive answer. Then, you will be asked to write your article. After my review, your article will be added to our private articles campaign spreadsheet.    Campaign 3: Twitter campaign  Rates :  Follow : 5 stakes Retweet : 20 stakes per RT Like : 5 stakes per like  Rules : This campaign is limited to 1000 participants. Only twitter accounts with more than 1000 followers will be allowed. Twitter campaign stakes ARE NOT distributed on a weekly basis. Do not RT and like tweets that are answers to other users. Do not RT and like tweets that are more than two weeks old. Do not post a Twitter report in this thread; we will analyze Twitter data on our own. We reserve the right to not consider your twitter account eligible for this campaign, even if you meet the prerequisites. You don't have to post reports in this thread! If at the end of the campaign, you tweeted more than 2000 times since your registration date, some of your retweets may not be counted. The same rule applies for likes. We won't accept participants that use Newbie, Jr. Member or Member bitcointalk accounts to list their twitter account. We will also remove you if your account is not active.  How to participate :  Fill this Google form : https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1wZKHVXPjTTqNobNryGxqYG8ZRrUGR5KGorT8vz7P53A/    Campaign 4: Translation campaign  Rules :  This campaign works with my Trusted Translators List. It means that translations slots will be reserved to my perpetual translators. If you don't see your language in my perpetual translators list, you can fill up the Google Form link and reserve a slot. A translation must be of a high quality ; not done by using translating tools. It must be finished before the start of ICO. You can reserve a translation by filling Google Form link, but if you did not translated your content (based on registration time), your reservation is over and another participant can take it from you. Once you have reserved an ANN thread translation, this reservation is valid for 2 days. Once you have reserved a whitepaper translation, this reservation is valid for 7days. Once you have reserved a one pager translation, this reservation is valid for 3 days. Once you have reserved a website translation, this reservation is valid for 5 days.  Trusted Translators List I work with a team of perpetual translators, who have proven that is it worthwhile to work with them. To save time and be sure about content translation quality, slots are reserved for those people. You can find a list of those perpetual translators here: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1_38Iifz48Qvwc_MxwvXztgi5s12FlwPt8qUPDCjVv2U/ If you don't see a perpetual translator for your language, you can now become a member of the team! Send me a PM with all your past work and I will see if you can be added to the list.  If those perpetual translators don't provide their work on time, the translation slot will be given to a backup translator. You can also find a list of backup translators in the same spreadsheet. If you don't see a backup translator for your language, you can now become a backup translator! Send me a PM with all your past work and I will see if you can be added to the list.  Rates :  1 ANN thread translation = 150 stakes 1 post from original poster in the translated ANN thread = 10 stakes 1 whitepaper translation = 1000 stakes 1 onepager translation = 400 stakes 1 website translation = 500 stakes  How to translate the whitepaper ?
